Enid.Enid Symphony Center: The Enid Symphony Center (also known as Enid Masonic Temple and the Knox Building), is a historic building located in Enid, Oklahoma. It is the home of the Enid Symphony Orchestra, and was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1984. The Italian Renaissance Revival building is also located within the Enid Downtown Historic District which became listed on the register in 2007.
